New York has been revealed as the top overseas destination for UK travellers in 2014 as they flock to the US to make the most of the strong British pound.

The exchange rate between sterling and the US dollar was at a five-year high in June, holidaymakers have snapped up trips taking them across the Pond.

The Big Apple beat 2013's champion Paris to the top spot, with Amsterdam making a surprise appearance in third place.

