The news comes as Hotels.com reveals the latest data from its Hotel Price Index; a biannual report based on actual prices paid in the first six months of 2014 compared with 2013.

Rounding off the top five was Dublin in fourth and the fun-filled Las Vegas in fifth. Further down the list, new entry Prague knocked Budapest (2013's No. 19 entry) from the list.

For overseas travellers to the UK, London remained the most visited city with Edinburgh coming in second.

